===Etymology===
Middle English, derived from Old English ''[[braegen]]'' and ''[[bregen]]''.

=== Noun ===
'''brain''' (''plural'' '''brains''')

#That part of the [[central nervous system]] of an [[animal]] located in the [[skull]] which controls the actions of the animal.
#An [[intelligent]] person.
#:''He was a total brain.''
#A person who provides the intelligence required for something.
#:''the brain behind the scheme''
#(''in plural'' '''brains''') [[Intellect]].
#:''He has a lot of brains.''
#By analogy with a human brain, the part of a [[machine]] or [[computer]] that performs [[calculation]]s.
#:''The computer's brain is capable of millions of calculations a second.''

